        "content": "<p>An elementary by still nice example is that any full, faithful and essentially surjective functor is an equivalence. It shows that (in the presence of choice), 'functorial' does not necessarily mean 'canonical'.</p>",
        "id": 261922314,
        "sender_full_name": "Fawzi Hreiki",
        "timestamp": 1637239804
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't understand the last sentence. How do you define \"canonical\"?</p>",
        "id": 261962381,
